<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12001e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12001e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12001e"> 1(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> all&eacute;e couverte / dolmen + couloir</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le <mark>dolmen</mark> se compose de pierres plant&eacute;es en terre, auxquelles on donne le nom de piliers, et qui supportent un nombre variable de blocs formant plafond horizontal. Il ressemble donc &agrave; une table et n&apos;est en principe qu&apos;une grossi&egrave;re chambre. L&apos;architecture de cette chambre varie <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>. Quand elle est pr&eacute;c&eacute;d&eacute;e d&apos;un <mark>couloir</mark> plus ou moins long, on l&apos;appelle alors: <mark>all&eacute;e couverte</mark> <br><font color="green">[A dolmen is made of stones set in earth that are called &lsquo;pillars&rsquo; and that support a variable number of blocks forming a horizontal platform. It thus resembles a table and is in principle just a crude chamber. The architecture of this chamber varies [&hellip;]</font>. When it is preceded by a passageway of whatever length it is called a covered passage.] <small> l'Abb&eacute; A. Millon, <a name="AMPB" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMPB"><cite title="source">Pauvres Pierres! Les Megalithes Bretons devant la science</cite></a> (n.d) 53</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
